Functional Interfaces

1- Exists since Java 1.0

2- A functional Interfaces (SAM) is an interface that has exactly one abstract method.

@FunctionalInterface:

- Optional annotation to signify an interface as Functional Interface.

-- New Functional Interface in Java-8 --

1- Consumer
2- Predicate
3- Function
4- Supplier

- Every interface has their own set of extension for improve

1- Consumer- BiConsumer
2- predicate- BiPredicate
3- Function- BiFunction, UnaryOperator, BinaryOperator


-- Function is Java is nothing, it only a method in a class ---